Owens thinks it's a great idea, and has Mason start writing an amendment while setting up a press conference with the dead girl's parents. Sarah leverages her relationship with Mason to get an exclusive interview with the parents, making herself look good to her network. Mason is upset when Sarah's questions lead the couple to admit that they don't really support parental responsibility. Mason's job is on the line, but he redeems himself by rewriting the amendment for Owens with an eye toward not unfairly blaming good parents with bad kids. Meanwhile, Sarah is troubled that she lied to the parents and said that she had recently lost a cousin close to her to violent crime to get them to open up. Pete gets a new high-powered job more on the merit of his sexual charm than anything else. Finley gets a job at the Smithsonian after showing a tour guide up with her knowledge of and excitement about history.

data: Also known as the pennant-fish and threadfin trevally.
Largest exclusively freshwater fish found in North America, measuring 8 to 10 feet.
Lives in fresh water and estuaries and only leaves these habitats to enter the Atlantic ocean to start its spawning migration to the Sargasso Sea.
Common name refers to its habit of snapping vigorously at fishery workers when caught. Even out of the water it is capable of lunging upwards to bite.
Atlantic bonito eat mackerel, menhaden, alewives, silversides, sand lance, and other fishes, as well as squid.

table-1333-867.caption: Contestants
data: Azaria (late 20s) is a voice over talent. Adriana (27) is a lecturer. Both of them are Malaysians. They met each other in university, and a rock solid friendship between them was cemented.

Priyanka (28) is pursuing her dreams of being an actress. Vineet (32) is a marketing manager. The chemistry between this couple can be seen through their teamwork during the show. Originally from India, they have chosen to make their home in Singapore.

Ines (23) is a golf athlete. Jennifer (24) is a fresh graduate. They were both beauty queens in the Miss Indonesia pageant in 2012, where they met. Owing to their differing personalities, Ines being cheeky and fun loving, and Jennifer being calm and strategic, they became fast friends.

Yvette (late 20s) is a fashion reporter/blogger. Sonya (22) is a model/actress. Yvette comes from Australia, and Sonya, a British/Thai ,met in 2012 when they bumped into each other in their shared apartment block in Singapore.

Adam (mid 20s) is a model from America. Adrian (mid 20s) is born in Malaysia, but grew up in suburban Australia. They both met in New York. For this competition, this duo are entirely focused on the goal: the chance to be on the show and to win the grand prize.

Sarah (24) is an internal consultant. Brian (27) is a chef. These Malaysian siblings have been close since young, and recently became even closer due to the death of their father. Their lack of experience in design motivates them further to do their best in designing their own destiny.

Deankie (23) and Tiara (23) have been friends since they were Art students. Both are Filipinos, and have been through tough times when they were younger - this brought them even closer, as they bonded over their love for Art and design.

Pearlyn (25) is a DJ from Singapore. Nara (34) is an emcee from Thailand. Both of them have similar personalities: loud, chirpy, and excited for what life has in store for them. Despite having zero knowledge when it comes to designing, this dynamic duo will not let that dampen their spirits and will make their design journey in the show worthwhile.

April (late 20s) is a media director from Great Britain. Jen (23) is an events manager from Malaysia. Having met each other 5 years ago in Melaka, they became great friends and were close-knit ever since. Jen sees herself as "water", and April as "fire", and they believe this balance in personalities makes them an awesome team.
